Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwi se Claim Will Be Void)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHEEKY TICO tracked the pace on the outside, engaged the leader in the three path around the turn, took the advantage coming to the quarter-pole, drifted in while shaking clear into upper stretch, responded well under the crop into the final furlong and drew away under strong urging. MIDNIGHT CHROME was hustled from the gate then showed speed, shied in nearing the seven-eighths, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked in the two path under threat from the winner to the outside on the turn, lost the advantage to that foe at the quarter-pole, moved out into upper stretch, chased into the final furlong and proved no match then just held the place. GHOSTLYPRINCE made contact with a foe at the start, settled off the early pace, moved closer with five furlongs to run, chased inside around the turn, came out into upper stretch and just missed the place while clear for the show. PAPI ON ICE dropped well back early, angled in leaving the chute, went two then three wide around the turn, drifted inward while remaining on his inside lead in upper stretch, swapped to the proper lead outside the sixteenth-pole and failed to threaten. SORPRESO was hustled from the gate then taken in hand while inside of a foe around the seven-eighths, dropped back while eased off the pace with six furlongs to run then moved out near the five-eighths, passed the nine-sixteenths under urging, went around the turn in the two to three path, came out into upper stretch and tired. BERT BERT BERT hit the inside of the gate at the start then bobbled hard while making contact with a foe, nearly unseated the rider as he was dislodged from his left iron and dangled over the right-side of his mount, had the jockey show great athleticism to regain balance in the center of the saddle then reached down to get his left foot back in the iron, spotted the field many lengths in the process, went three then two wide around the turn and trailed.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWENTY SIX BLACK coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing near the quarter pole, swung three wide into upper stretch in behind ITSALLCOMINTOGETHA, attempted to nudge his way out to the four path against FACTUALLY CORRECT and was denied the move, then successfully nudged his way to the four path at the eighth pole against that same rival, rallied to issue a challenge through the final sixteenth and was just up in the last strides to the wire. ELECTRIC STUFF coaxed from the start, dueled inside of ITSALLCOMINTOGETHA from the get go , came under coaxing near the quarter pole and got set down swinging just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in stubbornly clinging to the front until nailed in the last jumps to the finish. ITSALLCOMINTOGETHA shied out at the start filling some of the space left vacated by the outwards breaking NEW YORK PANTHER, dueled from the two path with the aforementioned foe to his inside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole before being let out spinning three wide for home, dug in under a drive continuing to knock heads through to the final seventy yards now fighting on between foes and was staved off to the end. FACTUALLY CORRECT coaxed from the gate, chased three wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four wide into upper stretch, got nudged at the three-sixteenths and denied the move, then got leaned on again and gave way to the five path allowing the eventual winner a seam, then weakened in the late stages. RIPE FOR MISCHIEF coaxed from the start, chased along the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and offered no response. TIE BREAKER chased five wide under coaxing from the three-eighths and weakened in the stretch. UNCLE MARTY got bumped twice at the start, chased just off the inside until tipped four wide through the turn, continued four wide for home and came up empty. NEW YORK PANTHER broke out at the start, chased just off the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung five wide for home, made no impact. IMPULSIVE SPENDING got bumped at the start by the aforementioned breaking outwards, chased three to four wide and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Distaff H. - Grade3 AQUEDUCT RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 100. Stakes Purse 150000. A HANDICAP FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $150 each which should accompany the nominations; $750 to pass the entry box and a n additional $750 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $750 in addition the entry and starting fees may be made at any time prior to the publication of weights. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, March 25, 2023 with 22 Nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOMMASGOTTARUN was hard held off the pace, ranged up in the four path on the turn, made a bid outside the quarter-pole, took over into upper stretch then shook clear, responded well under the crop in the final furlong and maintained a safe advantage under strong urging. HYDRA was hustled from the gate, pressed the pace between foes, vied in the two path while between rivals on the turn, dropped back in upper stretch and weakened while able to get the show. ROSSA VELOCE stumbled twice while making contact with a foe at the start, was taken up while trying to recover and very slow into stride, spotted the front many lengths, moved up on the outside, made a bid near the nine-sixteenths, vied in the four then three path around the turn and tired. GERRYMANDER was hustled to the front, set the pace under heavy pressure to her outside, vied along the rail through the turn and gave way. MERAVIGLIOSO was hustled from the start, pressed the pace on the outside, dropped back leaving the backstretch, was urged in the two to three path around the turn and came up empty. EASY TO BLESS was taken in hand early then settled at the rear, moved from the two path to the four path around the turn, angled out in upper stretch and was no factor.

LAUNCH CONTROL dueled from the two path with DISARMED to his outside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and took the inside route into upper stretch, got bumped at the three-sixteenths as his main pace rival came inwards, then leaned out just inside the eighth pole taking back a narrow advantage before being overhauled in tandem by the eventual winner, ran on to secure the place honors. SCHERZANDO turned his head to the near side then sprung to the off side at the break striking the stall door and getting away last conceding four lengths to the front before being able to settle into stride, chased four then three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, swung five wide into upper stretch and weakened.
